I"ü<p>Cablegram 42 [1] CANBERRA, 5 May 1944</p>

<p>MOST SECRET</p>

<p>For Curtin from Evatt.</p>

<p>Further to my 36. [2] Future of Italy. Defence Committee have submitted following observations upon Defence aspects of matter- (1) That no territories south of the Suez Canal should be left in Italian hands.</p>

<p>(2) That the disposition of Italian Overseas Possessions in the Mediterranean Area should be such that British Naval and Air Communications in the Mediterranean are adequately safeguarded.</p>

<p>[3]</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 Sent through the Commonwealth Govt Accredited Representative in London.</p>

<p>2 Document 125.</p>

<p>3 On 16 May Curtin advised Evatt that the question of the disposal of the Italian colonial empire had not come before the Conference, which had in fact â€˜confined its activities to the original purpose of an exchange of viewsâ€™. See cablegram 21 on file AA:A989, E44/455/9/1.</p>

